= Mirrored Swings

Mirrored swings consist of two opposite swinging subdivision systems (as seen in
Week 3). In order to maintain their synchronicity, their respective amounts of
swing are inverted.

This implies that when morphing through the range of swing, the two parts are
morphing in opposite directions.


 #figure(
  image("Figures/mirror2.png")
)


There are two main approaches to practice and experience the *mirror*:

+ *The low subdivisions emerge from the high:* \
  This is achieved through accentuation of the selected onsets of the high
  subdivision system:


 #figure(
  image("Figures/mirror3a.png")
)

+ *The high subdivisions emerge from the low:* \
  This is achieved by adding a grace note in place of the high-subdivision notes
  that do not pertain (or are not in sync) to the low subdivisions:


 #figure(
  image("Figures/mirror3b.png")
)

